The paper deals with image classification using deep convolutional neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed approach involves reducing the dimensionality of internal fully connected layers and modelling the resulting features using a Gaussian mixture model, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of datasets such as Fish and UEC FOOD-100, which are commonly used in multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR) research.
